## Verify in Jaeger UI
# Step A: Open Jaeger
Open: http://localhost:16686

# Step B: Check services are present
Click the Service dropdown. You should see the same services as Phase 1:

frontend
checkoutservice
productcatalogservice
currencyservice
paymentservice
If the dropdown is empty, wait 2–3 minutes for the load generator to produce traffic.

# Step C: Compare trace counts
Select frontend, set Lookback to Last 15 Minutes, set Limit to 1000
Click Find Traces
Count the traces — this number should be noticeably less than your Phase 1 baseline
For example, if Phase 1 showed ~200 traces in 15 minutes, Phase 3 should show ~100 traces (roughly 50% with default threshold=0.5).

# Step D: Verify traces are complete
Click on any trace
Check the waterfall view — you should see all spans of the trace present
This confirms the trace-level caching is working (all spans of a sampled trace are kept together)
# Step E: Check that errors are captured
In the search bar, set Tags to: otel.status_code=ERROR or error=true
If there are any error traces, they should ALL appear (because force_sample_errors=True)

## Collect Phase 3 Metrics
# Get sidecar metrics
# Get the latest metrics line from sidecar logs
docker compose logs fsbs-sidecar 2>&1 | findstr "FSBS METRICS"

## Collect data for phase3_metrics.txt file
# 1. Grab the absolute latest metrics line from the sidecar
$latestLog = docker compose logs fsbs-sidecar 2>&1 | Select-String "FSBS METRICS" | Select-Object -Last 1

# 2. Query Jaeger for the exact number of traces in the last 15 minutes
$jaegerResponse = (Invoke-WebRequest "http://localhost:16686/api/traces?service=frontend&limit=5000&lookback=15m" -UseBasicParsing -ErrorAction SilentlyContinue).Content
$traceCount = ($jaegerResponse | ConvertFrom-Json).data.Count

# 3. Print it out nicely
Write-Host "`n=== AUTOMATED PHASE 3 METRICS ===" -ForegroundColor Cyan
Write-Host "SIDECAR LOGS: " -ForegroundColor Yellow
Write-Host $latestLog.Line
Write-Host "`nJAEGER DB: " -ForegroundColor Yellow
Write-Host "Traces found (last 15m): $traceCount"
Write-Host "=================================`n" -ForegroundColor Cyan

## Experiment: See the Threshold Effect
# Try different thresholds to see FSBS adapt:

# High threshold (sample less — aggressive filtering)
docker compose down fsbs-sidecar

# Edit docker-compose.yaml: change FSBS_THRESHOLD to "0.8"
# Or use command line override:
docker compose up -d

# To quickly test, edit the FSBS_THRESHOLD value in docker-compose.yaml
  fsbs-sidecar:
    ...
    environment:
      FSBS_THRESHOLD: "0.8"    # ← change this

docker compose up --build -d fsbs-sidecar
docker compose restart frontend productcatalogservice checkoutservice currencyservice paymentservice

# Wait 2 minutes, then check
docker compose logs fsbs-sidecar 2>&1 | findstr "FSBS METRICS"

# With threshold=0.8, you should see span_pass_rate drop to ~20–30%.

